abstract: The White House’s attempt to impose a more disciplined approach to communications about the virus was undermined by President Trump, who complained the news media was overstating the threat.
snippet: The White House’s attempt to impose a more disciplined approach to communications about the virus was undermined by President Trump, who complained the news media was overstating the threat.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House moved on Thursday to tighten control of coronavirus messaging by government health officials and scientists, directing them to coordinate all statements and public appearances with the office of Vice President Mike Pence, according to several officials familiar with the new approach.

abstract: A Bernie Sanders administration might logically start with a roughly $300 billion federal jobs guarantee, a cornerstone of worker protection, says a key adviser to the front-runner in the U.S. Democratic presidential nominating race.
snippet: A Bernie Sanders administration might logically start with a roughly $300 billion federal jobs guarantee, a cornerstone of worker protection, says a key adviser to the front-runner in the U.S. Democratic presidential nominating race.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Bernie Sanders administration might logically start with a roughly $300 billion federal jobs guarantee, a cornerstone of worker protection, says a key adviser to the front-runner in the U.S. Democratic presidential nominating race.
headline_main: Sanders Presidency Could Start With U.S. Jobs Program, Then Scale Up
headline_print_headline: Sanders Presidency Could Start With U.S. Jobs Program, Then Scale Up

abstract: Readers discuss Thomas L. Friedman’s idea for a “national unity” ticket that includes many of the contenders as well as Mitt Romney and AOC in cabinet posts.

abstract: Plans to open what could be the nation's first medically supervised injection site in Philadelphia were put on hold Thursday night amid strenuous opposition from a federal prosecutor and residents of the neighborhood where it would have been located.
snippet: Plans to open what could be the nation's first medically supervised injection site in Philadelphia were put on hold Thursday night amid strenuous opposition from a federal prosecutor and residents of the neighborhood where it would have been locat...
lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — Plans to open what could be the nation's first medically supervised injection site in Philadelphia were put on hold Thursday night amid strenuous opposition from a federal prosecutor and residents of the neighborhood where it would have been located.
headline_main: US Supervised Injection Site Put on Hold Amid Opposition
headline_print_headline: US Supervised Injection Site Put on Hold Amid Opposition

abstract: National and regional leaders are trading blame, with the dispute centered around whether Lombardy had inflated the threat by testing too much.
snippet: National and regional leaders are trading blame, with the dispute centered around whether Lombardy had inflated the threat by testing too much.
lead_paragraph: MILAN — On the sixth floor of a skyscraper, two dozen epidemiologists and public health experts form the nerve center of the effort to contain a coronavirus outbreak in Italy that has alarmed Europe and put the wealthy Lombardy region at the center of global concern.

abstract: U.S. stocks plummeted on Thursday as fears about the effect of the coronavirus outbreak on economic growth flared even as U.S. officials pledged that they were stepping up efforts to safeguard Americans from the virus' spread.
snippet: U.S. stocks plummeted on Thursday as fears about the effect of the coronavirus outbreak on economic growth flared even as U.S. officials pledged that they were stepping up efforts to safeguard Americans from the virus' spread.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK/WASHINGTON — U.S. stocks plummeted on Thursday as fears about the effect of the coronavirus outbreak on economic growth flared even as U.S. officials pledged that they were stepping up efforts to safeguard Americans from the virus' spread.
headline_main: Stocks Plunge on Coronavirus Fears Even as U.S. Ramps Up Fight Against Spread
headline_print_headline: Stocks Plunge on Coronavirus Fears Even as U.S. Ramps Up Fight Against Spread

abstract: Fifty former European prime ministers and foreign ministers have condemned U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan in an open letter, saying it would create an apartheid-like situation in occupied Palestinian territory.
snippet: Fifty former European prime ministers and foreign ministers have condemned U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan in an open letter, saying it would create an apartheid-like situation in occupied Palestinian territory.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Fifty former European prime ministers and foreign ministers have condemned U.S. President Donald Trump's Middle East peace plan in an open letter, saying it would create an apartheid-like situation in occupied Palestinian territory.
headline_main: Former European Leaders Say Trump's Middle East Peace Plan Akin to Apartheid
headline_print_headline: Former European Leaders Say Trump's Middle East Peace Plan Akin to Apartheid

abstract: One by one, more and more countries are reporting cases of the new coronavirus. Governments and doctors on the front lines are scrambling for solutions and everyday life around the globe is being disrupted in a manner that's not been seen in recent times.

headline_main: What's Happening: Virus Forges On, as World Hunts Solutions

abstract: In the Middle East, even virus outbreaks are political.

abstract: The Federal Reserve may need to move aggressively to cut borrowing costs to cushion the economy from the effects of the rapid spread of the new coronavirus, which sent global stocks tumbling this week.
snippet: The Federal Reserve may need to move aggressively to cut borrowing costs to cushion the economy from the effects of the rapid spread of the new coronavirus, which sent global stocks tumbling this week.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO/MEXICO CITY — The Federal Reserve may need to move aggressively to cut borrowing costs to cushion the economy from the effects of the rapid spread of the new coronavirus, which sent global stocks tumbling this week.
headline_main: Fed Seen Cutting Rates Amid Virus Threat, Low Inflation
headline_print_headline: Fed Seen Cutting Rates Amid Virus Threat, Low Inflation
